Present the specific nature of social workers' activities in the context of a multicultural environment, behavioural and social norms related to cultural differences. Provide the necessary knowledge and skills for teaching in a multilingual and multicultural group.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Present the specific nature of social workers' activities in the context of a multicultural environment, behavioural and social norms related to cultural differences. Provide the necessary knowledge and skills for teaching in a multilingual and multicultural group.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) be able to detect a person in crisis and react to this situation; 2) analyse and design techniques of community work as one of the classic methods of social work according to practical needs; 3) know the legal bases for community engagement (3 different levels of engagement); 4) know and apply different forms of communication and behaviour arising from the specific nature of human groups; 5) be able to design an environment that supports open communication between people and groups; 6) know the intrinsic nature of activities in a multicultural environment.
